arlington west : the film is a 2006 documentary about the iraq war by peter &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and sally marr . the title refers to arlington west , the " temporary cemeteries " in santa barbara and santa monica , california which serve as &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; to those who have been killed in iraq . the film features 105 interviews , mostly with young soldiers who have served in iraq , talking about their experiences there . it also features members of gold star families for peace , whose sons or daughters died in iraq . among these parents are cindy sheehan , fernando &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , jane bright , bill mitchell , vickie castro , nadia &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , and karen meredith .